FBIS3-37729 "drsov036_e_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-036 Document Type:Daily Report 23 Feb 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs Zlenko Advocates Political Solution for Yugoslav Crisis WS2202210594 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in Ukrainian 1900 GMT 22 Feb 94 WS2202210594 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network Language: Ukrainian Article Type:BFN [Text] Ukrainian Foreign Minister Anatoliy Zlenko is continuing his visit to Germany. In an interview to the leading German newspaper FRANKFURTER ALLGEMEINE ZEITUNG, Anatoliy Zlenko said: We did not make a mistake when we thought that the Yugoslav crisis should be settled by political means. A bombardment can only escalate the conflict. The Ukrainian foreign minister emphasized that the search is under way right now for political resolution of the Balkan problem, which is evidenced by the Russian proposal. Asked about Ukraine's participation in the UN-sponsored peace keeping mission in Yugoslavia, Anatoliy Zlenko said that the Ukrainian contingent of the blue helmets will increase by an additional 800 people.
